description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a 12 month Secondment/ Fixed Term contract opportunity for an enthusiastic, dynamic and motivated leader to join our Diabetes Clinical Nurse Specialist team at Withybush General Hospital. The post will be on a full time, 37.5 hours per week basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have to be compassionate, enthusiastic, and a motivated leader who has previous band 6 experience in the field of Diabetes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a Hywel Dda University Health Board employee and are applying for this post as a secondment, agreement for the secondment is needed from your current manager prior to application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to demonstrate excellent leadership skills and communication skills, be a forward thinking individual and strive for high standards of patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work autonomously through providing specialist advice, education and promote effective diabetes care across secondary care, working closely with all members of the multidisciplinary team. The post holder will be expected manage a small team, to deliver education and training to both staff and patients to promote a high quality of care across the county. We aim to provide a service which is tailored to individual needs as well as ensuring our staff are supported through clinical supervision, education and ongoing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Gina Hughes Senior Nurse Manager Unscheduled Care for any further information on 01437 773008 or Email Gina.hughes@wales.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on Friday 27th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
